definitions.definition: The throne name of a pharaoh , the fourth of the five names of the royal titulary , traditionally encircled by a cartouche and preceded by the title nswt-bjtj .
examples: Tutankhamun 's praenomen or throne name was Nebkheperrure, "Lord of the forms of Ra ".

definitions.definition: The genus name in a binomial scientific name .
examples: In the name Tyrannosaurus rex , "Tyrannosaurus" is the praenomen .

main_definition: ( historical ) An Ancient Roman given name .
secondary_definitions: ( historical ) The throne name of a pharaoh , the fourth of the five names of the royal titulary , traditionally encircled by a cartouche and preceded by the title nswt-bjtj .
( zoology ) The genus name in a binomial scientific name .
